00:29:07,506 --> 00:29:09,501
What is it?

545
00:29:09,501 --> 00:29:10,501
Fat.

546
00:29:11,048 --> 00:29:12,048
Dark.

547
00:29:12,718 --> 00:29:13,718
Likes to eat vegetables.

548
00:29:15,067 --> 00:29:15,938
Chaba.

549
00:29:15,938 --> 00:29:16,938
Chaba what?

550
00:29:17,414 --> 00:29:18,414
It’s a guinea pig!

551
00:29:22,489 --> 00:29:28,958
Second one...what’s afraid of sugar,

552
00:29:28,958 --> 00:29:30,958
and always carries an injection?

553
00:29:33,112 --> 00:29:35,112
That’s Chaba, of course. An insulin syringe.

554
00:29:37,141 --> 00:29:37,808
Wrong.

555
00:29:37,808 --> 00:29:38,676
Huh?

556
00:29:38,676 --> 00:29:40,676
A plastic surgeon on a diet.

557
00:29:43,866 --> 00:29:44,866
The other side as well...

558
00:29:47,415 --> 00:29:54,328
Third one, what has the same name as a cartoon elephant?

559
00:29:54,328 --> 00:29:57,284
Chaba.

560
00:29:57,284 --> 00:30:01,285
What? It’s Dumbo, not Chaba. Wrong.

561
00:30:03,078 --> 00:30:04,109
Why is everything “Chaba” with you?

562
00:30:04,109 --> 00:30:05,855
If it’s going to be like this, just play the two of you.

563
00:30:05,855 --> 00:30:07,855
Come on, let’s go for a walk on the beach.

564
00:30:11,286 --> 00:30:13,239
Why is everything Chaba? Come here.

565
00:30:13,239 --> 00:30:14,196
Chaba?

566
00:30:14,196 --> 00:30:15,506
Well, that’s just the only answer I can think of.

567
00:30:15,506 --> 00:30:16,260
Chaba, Chaba.

568
00:30:16,260 --> 00:30:17,575
Dumbo is not Chaba.

569
00:30:17,575 --> 00:30:18,488
Which Chaba do you even mean?

570
00:30:18,488 --> 00:30:19,522
Chaba Kaew.

571
00:30:19,522 --> 00:30:21,312
Never heard of Chaba Kaew. Never watched it.

572
00:30:21,312 --> 00:30:22,102
Khan Kluay.

573
00:30:22,102 --> 00:30:24,891
Never watched it. I only watch foreign movies, foreign cartoons.

574
00:30:24,891 --> 00:30:25,891
Boring.

575
00:30:27,002 --> 00:30:28,002
Please fasten your seatbelt.

576
00:30:31,595 --> 00:30:32,595
Please fasten your seatbelt, sir.

577
00:30:37,072 --> 00:30:39,072
Maria, please come here a moment.

578
00:30:39,421 --> 00:30:41,421
The passenger refuses to fasten their seatbelt.

579
00:30:44,168 --> 00:30:45,156
He already did.

580
00:30:45,156 --> 00:30:47,270
Oh, he really did.

581
00:30:47,270 --> 00:30:49,270
Wait, that’s not a seatbelt.

582
00:30:52,221 --> 00:30:53,286
It’s a gun.

583
00:30:53,286 --> 00:30:53,756
Hey!

584
00:30:53,756 --> 00:30:54,756
Nobody move.

585
00:30:56,624 --> 00:30:57,701
Hand over all your valuables.

586
00:30:57,701 --> 00:30:58,701
I said don’t move!

587
00:31:00,692 --> 00:31:01,692
Hey, I said don’t move!

588
00:31:03,958 --> 00:31:04,958
Stop.

589
00:31:06,033 --> 00:31:07,033
Stop.

590
00:31:07,419 --> 00:31:08,419
I said stop!

591
00:31:08,927 --> 00:31:09,927
We've stopped...

592
00:31:11,400 --> 00:31:13,106
Hand it over. Now!

593
00:31:13,106 --> 00:31:15,106
Hey, hand it over. Quickly!

594
00:31:16,180 --> 00:31:17,180
Don’t drag your feet.

595
00:31:18,935 --> 00:31:20,843
Don’t look, just hand it over! Quickly!

596
00:31:20,843 --> 00:31:22,843
If you have something, give it all.

597
00:31:23,029 --> 00:31:24,029
Hurry! Hurry!

598
00:31:24,663 --> 00:31:25,451
Where are you going?

599
00:31:25,451 --> 00:31:26,451
Is that all?

600
00:31:26,801 --> 00:31:27,801
Help out here!

601
00:31:28,229 --> 00:31:30,229
Hey! I said be quiet!

602
00:31:30,540 --> 00:31:31,414
Didn’t you hear me? Do you see what this is, huh?

603
00:31:31,414 --> 00:31:32,890
Nope. I don’t see it.

604
00:31:32,890 --> 00:31:34,890
It’s a bullet, damn it, not candy!

605
00:31:43,958 --> 00:31:45,707
Hey, what’s going on?

606
00:31:45,707 --> 00:31:46,707
I’m so scared.

607
00:31:51,852 --> 00:31:54,852
We’ve regained control of the situation.

608
00:31:55,845 --> 00:31:56,845
Applause, please.

609
00:31:59,794 --> 00:32:03,794
This is Porn Airline.

610
00:32:12,414 --> 00:32:14,291
Where’s Chai gone?

611
00:32:14,291 --> 00:32:17,279
He ran off to bed.

612
00:32:17,279 --> 00:32:21,279
I just heard him complain he didn’t sleep at all last night. No idea what he was up to.

613
00:32:26,792 --> 00:32:27,792
Tid-Gift.

614
00:32:29,583 --> 00:32:30,583
Why are you sleeping here?

615
00:32:35,573 --> 00:32:37,402
And why does this salad have Thai eggplant in it?

616
00:32:37,402 --> 00:32:41,402
It’s Chaba’s Thai eggplant salad. Who ordered this?

617
00:32:41,869 --> 00:32:42,869
Was it Sky just now?

618
00:32:43,422 --> 00:32:45,422
Uh, no way.

619
00:32:46,815 --> 00:32:48,815
I think the chef made a mistake.

620
00:32:49,725 --> 00:32:51,725
It's probably made food for pigs.

621
00:32:52,593 --> 00:32:54,593
Shall I return it for you?

622
00:32:57,343 --> 00:32:58,343
It’s good, right?

623
00:32:59,575 --> 00:33:03,575
Sky, if you miss Chaba, you can just tell us.

624
00:33:04,761 --> 00:33:07,227
We miss Chaba too.

625
00:33:07,227 --> 00:33:09,227
Why would I miss her?

626
00:33:12,978 --> 00:33:13,978
Can I borrow your lipstick? My lips are dry.

627
00:33:14,810 --> 00:33:15,810
Go ahead.

628
00:33:17,481 --> 00:33:18,481
Oh!

629
00:33:20,398 --> 00:33:22,398
This is Chaba’s insulin pen.

630
00:33:31,072 --> 00:33:36,072
She forgot it and didn’t take it with her.

631
00:33:38,225 --> 00:33:41,225
If her blood sugar spikes, what’s she gonna do?

632
00:33:42,776 --> 00:33:44,776
Chaba, don’t die!

633
00:33:56,160 --> 00:33:57,160
No.

634
00:33:58,155 --> 00:34:01,068
I’m not caring about Chaba anymore.

635
00:34:01,068 --> 00:34:04,068
Waiter, bring me another case.

636
00:34:05,576 --> 00:34:07,576
You guys drink with me too.

637
00:34:17,683 --> 00:34:19,683
My teeth, my teeth!

638
00:34:32,591 --> 00:34:35,106
This trip was so damn exhausting.

639
00:34:35,106 --> 00:34:37,934
Did Mr. Glam give us a gift or a punishment?

640
00:34:37,934 --> 00:34:40,842
Yeah, and where did everyone else go?

641
00:34:40,842 --> 00:34:42,630
Chai had to rush to the office.

642
00:34:42,630 --> 00:34:45,630
And the other two, just let them sleep at the hotel.

643
00:34:48,340 --> 00:34:49,340
I wonder how Chaba’s doing.

644
00:34:50,851 --> 00:34:51,851
What?

645
00:34:59,001 --> 00:35:00,001
Yes.

646
00:35:00,390 --> 00:35:01,390
Okay.

647
00:35:01,826 --> 00:35:02,826
Oh, my ride’s here.

648
00:35:03,894 --> 00:35:04,894
I’m heading off.

649
00:35:06,641 --> 00:35:08,641
Bye-bye, see you.

650
00:35:49,885 --> 00:35:53,885
Today we handled the situation really well. I’m impressed.

651
00:35:55,187 --> 00:35:57,692
Maria, actually, I was the one...

652
00:35:59,689 --> 00:36:02,636
Who’s that? Looks kind of weird.

653
00:36:02,636 --> 00:36:05,636
And that bag looks weird too. Fake, right?

654
00:36:07,503 --> 00:36:08,503
It’s real!

655
00:36:08,776 --> 00:36:14,444
Oh, why are you the only one left? Isn’t it lonely sitting here alone?

656
00:36:14,444 --> 00:36:18,444
Or did everyone else wise up and stop hanging out with you like Chaba did?

657
00:36:18,912 --> 00:36:19,904
Let’s go.

658
00:36:19,904 --> 00:36:23,453
Chaba, you make a very good point. I agree.

659
00:36:23,453 --> 00:36:26,127
We shouldn’t waste our time on people like this.

660
00:36:26,127 --> 00:36:27,127
That's not it.

661
00:36:27,319 --> 00:36:31,319
Oh, not a person, just looks like one?

662
00:36:32,388 --> 00:36:33,661
Shall we go have lunch?

663
00:36:33,661 --> 00:36:41,661
Ooooh, savage. We eat rice, and they can eat grass.

664
00:36:43,892 --> 00:36:45,883
You’re so good at making connections

665
00:36:45,883 --> 00:36:48,871
pigs, dogs, chickens...

666
00:36:48,871 --> 00:36:50,942
Better than some people who can’t make any connections.

667
00:36:50,942 --> 00:36:52,491
Sitting all alone for ages.

668
00:36:52,491 --> 00:36:54,491
Can’t figure it out? No one wants you anymore.

669
00:37:04,124 --> 00:37:06,124
Have your new friend give you the shot instead.

670
00:37:17,517 --> 00:37:18,517
I forgot my bag.

671
00:37:32,632 --> 00:37:34,632
Uh, excuse me, sir.

672
00:37:35,503 --> 00:37:36,503
Sir.

673
00:37:37,536 --> 00:37:38,536
Sir.

674
00:37:38,851 --> 00:37:39,851
Sir.

675
00:37:42,401 --> 00:37:44,401
Sorry, I’m awake now.

676
00:37:45,472 --> 00:37:47,464
That’s okay, you can sleep here.

677
00:37:47,464 --> 00:37:50,293
I just wanted to ask, have you seen the rat glue trap?

678
00:37:50,293 --> 00:37:51,206
Huh?

679
00:37:51,206 --> 00:37:52,206
Yes, the rat glue trap.

680
00:37:57,357 --> 00:38:00,357
Hey, have you seen the rat glue trap?

681
00:38:04,311 --> 00:38:05,311
Nope.

682
00:38:05,738 --> 00:38:06,685
We haven’t seen it.

683
00:38:06,685 --> 00:38:07,685
That’s alright, thank you.

684
00:38:13,031 --> 00:38:17,031
Why did they ask me? I’m a paying customer. Glue trap?

685
00:38:24,106 --> 00:38:25,106
I found the rat glue trap.

686
00:38:25,337 --> 00:38:26,337
Huh?

687
00:38:26,451 --> 00:38:27,451
Then take it to them.

688
00:38:29,442 --> 00:38:30,442
It’s right here.

689
00:38:30,874 --> 00:38:31,874
Here you are, oh wow!

690
00:38:32,703 --> 00:38:33,650
Shit.

691
00:38:33,650 --> 00:38:36,683
Hey! When did I sit on it?

692
00:38:36,683 --> 00:38:37,436
No idea.

693
00:38:37,436 --> 00:38:38,436
Kreetha, help me pull it off.

694
00:38:38,906 --> 00:38:39,906
Alright, come here.

695
00:38:42,286 --> 00:38:43,286
Hey! Pull it gently!

696
00:38:43,357 --> 00:38:44,142
One, two, pull!

697
00:38:44,142 --> 00:38:45,142
It’s really stuck.

698
00:38:50,054 --> 00:38:51,054
Damn.

699
00:38:52,527 --> 00:38:53,480
You get up.

700
00:38:53,480 --> 00:38:54,480
No, you get up.

701
00:38:54,711 --> 00:38:55,711
I’m trying!

702
00:38:56,059 --> 00:38:58,059
Fine, get up together. One, two, three!

703
00:39:02,005 --> 00:39:05,005
Oh! Whoa!

704
00:39:05,952 --> 00:39:06,952
Just a second.

705
00:39:08,064 --> 00:39:09,064
Why are you holding on? Let go!

706
00:39:16,454 --> 00:39:18,454
Here you go, here you go.

707
00:39:19,001 --> 00:39:20,001
No, no, no.

708
00:39:22,358 --> 00:39:25,358
Welcome, lovebird couple!

709
00:39:30,710 --> 00:39:31,710
This way, this way!

710
00:39:32,023 --> 00:39:33,023
Walk properly, will you?

711
00:39:43,338 --> 00:39:46,048
Chaba, you are so lucky.

712
00:39:46,048 --> 00:39:48,048
You don’t have to be friends with people like that anymore, you know?

713
00:39:50,035 --> 00:39:54,035
Right, and what kind of friend leaves something like this for you?

714
00:39:54,068 --> 00:39:56,068
Completely useless. And what is it anyway?

715
00:39:58,221 --> 00:40:01,017
Wow, the new mascara model, never seen it before.

716
00:40:01,017 --> 00:40:02,017
Oh, it's insulin.

717
00:40:03,925 --> 00:40:04,925
Important stuff.

718
00:40:05,114 --> 00:40:07,185
Don’t bother with people like that.

719
00:40:07,185 --> 00:40:09,174
We’re not going anywhere.

720
00:40:09,174 --> 00:40:11,686
You’ll always have us by your side.

721
00:40:11,686 --> 00:40:13,323
But earlier, on the plane…

722
00:40:13,323 --> 00:40:14,317
What about it?

723
00:40:14,317 --> 00:40:18,310
When you ran to the back, wasn’t it…

724
00:40:18,310 --> 00:40:22,310
Friends forever!

725
00:40:24,898 --> 00:40:25,898
Oh, one second.

726
00:40:26,886 --> 00:40:27,886
Hello?

727
00:40:30,479 --> 00:40:31,479
Yes.

728
00:40:34,266 --> 00:40:35,131
Yes.

729
00:40:35,131 --> 00:40:37,483
Yes, this is the crew who helped the passenger on the plane.

730
00:40:37,483 --> 00:40:38,483
Who is it?

731
00:40:39,828 --> 00:40:40,828
Police.

732
00:40:41,015 --> 00:40:41,888
Police.

733
00:40:41,888 --> 00:40:42,757
Oh!

734
00:40:42,757 --> 00:40:45,150
Maybe they’re calling to praise the three of us for helping the passengers.

735
00:40:45,150 --> 00:40:46,150
Yes, yes.

736
00:40:46,982 --> 00:40:50,983
Tell the police Team Maria is always happy to help.

737
00:40:52,490 --> 00:40:53,490
Yes, officer?

738
00:40:53,763 --> 00:40:57,550
Huh? The passenger is dead?

739
00:40:57,550 --> 00:41:01,300
Now the three of us are murder suspects.

740
00:41:01,300 --> 00:41:02,771
What?

741
00:41:02,771 --> 00:41:04,078
Oh my god, Chaba!

742
00:41:04,078 --> 00:41:05,834
Why did you do that?

743
00:41:05,834 --> 00:41:09,834
What? My god, Chaba, why would you do that?

744
00:41:10,061 --> 00:41:12,771
I told you not to overdo it.

745
00:41:12,771 --> 00:41:16,150
We told you, Chaba, don’t go too far.

746
00:41:16,150 --> 00:41:17,702
And look what you’ve done.

747
00:41:17,702 --> 00:41:20,213
And look what you’ve done, Chaba.

748
00:41:20,213 --> 00:41:22,607
Shit, and now he's dead.

749
00:41:22,607 --> 00:41:23,920
Fuck.

750
00:41:23,920 --> 00:41:25,671
He's a dead man now.

751
00:41:25,671 --> 00:41:27,338
I didn’t use an F word.

752
00:41:27,338 --> 00:41:28,083
Oh.

753
00:41:28,083 --> 00:41:29,995
It’s all your fault, Chaba.

754
00:41:29,995 --> 00:41:33,615
It’s entirely your fault, nothing to do with the two of us, Chaba.

755
00:41:33,615 --> 00:41:35,615
Weren’t we on the same team?

756
00:41:37,092 --> 00:41:38,092
It’s okay.

757
00:41:38,243 --> 00:41:39,243
No one actually called.

758
00:41:40,038 --> 00:41:42,038
See? Did anyone call?

759
00:41:42,507 --> 00:41:45,507
Oops, we did it again.

760
00:41:46,334 --> 00:41:48,487
Two-faced snakes.

761
00:41:48,487 --> 00:41:50,195
Pretending to wish me well,

762
00:41:50,195 --> 00:41:52,195
but actually wishing me harm.

763
00:41:54,942 --> 00:41:58,942
That’s nothing like my old friend.

764
00:42:00,571 --> 00:42:04,571
No matter how messed up her face was, she never had a bad heart.

765
00:42:04,726 --> 00:42:06,796
She never lied to me like this.

766
00:42:06,796 --> 00:42:10,182
Unlike you two, claiming to be friends

767
00:42:10,182 --> 00:42:13,408
but when the time comes, you just save yourselves.

768
00:42:13,408 --> 00:42:15,881
I don’t think we can be together anymore.

769
00:42:15,881 --> 00:42:16,830
Are you saying…

770
00:42:16,830 --> 00:42:18,499
Yes, I’d like…

771
00:42:18,499 --> 00:42:21,499
A chance to keep working here?

772
00:42:22,645 --> 00:42:26,910
I’m sorry, but you’re not Porn Airline cabin crew material.

773
00:42:26,910 --> 00:42:29,581
No, I mean I resign. I quit.

774
00:42:29,581 --> 00:42:31,777
Oh, really? You don't have the guts.

775
00:42:31,777 --> 00:42:33,355
No, I quit! I resign!

776
00:42:33,355 --> 00:42:35,355
I’ve decided, you need to go home.

777
00:42:37,232 --> 00:42:38,232
Bye-bye.

778
00:42:44,179 --> 00:42:46,179
I said I quit!

779
00:42:47,289 --> 00:42:49,289
I’ve quit five times already!

780
00:43:03,481 --> 00:43:04,481
Oh shit, shit, shit! Oh!

781
00:43:05,870 --> 00:43:06,870
It’s burning, burning!

782
00:43:08,651 --> 00:43:09,651
Shit, shit, oh!

783
00:43:11,281 --> 00:43:12,281
Thank you.

784
00:43:15,668 --> 00:43:17,668
The veggies are all cooked now, just eat them.

785
00:43:22,658 --> 00:43:25,968
You’re unemployed now, aren’t you? What’s next for you?

786
00:43:25,968 --> 00:43:29,968
How do you know? Don’t tell me you guessed.

787
00:43:31,318 --> 00:43:32,318
I overheard.

788
00:43:34,186 --> 00:43:35,186
Just say it straight.

789
00:43:36,016 --> 00:43:38,016
I’m not a fake person, right?

790
00:43:39,573 --> 00:43:43,161
Yeah, true. You just say what you think.

791
00:43:43,161 --> 00:43:45,161
That I became a flight attendant because of you.

792
00:43:45,909 --> 00:43:47,909
Well, it’s true.

793
00:43:48,778 --> 00:43:51,885
You only got into Glamorous Airline because of me, right?

794
00:43:51,885 --> 00:43:54,473
You never even thought about becoming a flight attendant.

795
00:43:54,473 --> 00:43:57,473
Oh sure, Miss Talented, only you can do anything.

796
00:44:00,579 --> 00:44:04,580
But actually, they hired you because of you, right?

797
00:44:04,847 --> 00:44:07,195
When the HR guy choked on a bun,

798
00:44:07,195 --> 00:44:10,061
if you hadn’t saved his life,

799
00:44:10,061 --> 00:44:13,332
he wouldn’t have lived to hire me.

800
00:44:13,332 --> 00:44:15,332
Then you should thank me.

801
00:44:24,440 --> 00:44:25,338
Those meatballs look good.

802
00:44:25,338 --> 00:44:28,053
That one’s raw. Wait, I’ll grill it for you.

803
00:44:28,053 --> 00:44:30,289
Teach me, I don’t know how.

804
00:44:30,289 --> 00:44:33,289
Why teach you when I’m already grilling it for you right here?

805
00:44:42,357 --> 00:44:43,357
Do you think this is kind of yuri?

806
00:44:44,147 --> 00:44:46,147
Ew, I’m gonna puke. Gross.

807
00:44:47,299 --> 00:44:48,299
Hey.

808
00:44:48,611 --> 00:44:49,611
What?

809
00:44:49,681 --> 00:44:52,681
Spill the tea about Maria and Yard for me.

810
00:44:52,753 --> 00:44:54,622
And when you’re done,

811
00:44:54,622 --> 00:44:58,609
I’ve got gossip about Tid-Gift and Chai to tell you.

812
00:44:58,609 --> 00:45:01,155
What? What did I miss?

813
00:45:01,155 --> 00:45:02,155
A lot.

